---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Jason Griess and the Topophilia project.">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">

    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-2">
      About
    </h1>
    <div class="w-10 h-0.5 bg-forest mb-10"></div>

    <div class="prose prose-stone prose-topophilia max-w-none space-y-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-stone-700">

      <p>
        I'm Jason Griess, and I make things about cities. Maps, dashboards, data tools,
        essays — whatever helps people see what's actually happening in their neighborhood
        and what it could become.
      </p>

      <p>
        I live in Pittsburgh, which is a good city to care about. It has real problems
        that data can illuminate and real people who are trying to fix them. A lot of what
        I build starts with a question I had as a resident: where are the playgrounds that
        won't cook my kid? What's actually being built in my neighborhood? Where can I bike
        without arriving drenched?
      </p>

      <p>
        The animating idea behind all of this is that cities can be genuinely cozy — not
        just functional or efficient, but friendly, walkable, affordable, and human in
        scale. That's not nostalgia. It's a design choice, and it's one that good data and
        good policy can actually push toward.
      </p>

      <p>
        Topophilia is where I publish the work and think out loud about it.
        The name comes from geographer Yi-Fu Tuan's term for the emotional bond between
        people and place. That felt right.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink mt-10 mb-3">Currently</h2>
      <p>
        I'm building civic technology tools for Pittsburgh — maps and dashboards that make
        invisible city systems legible to residents and decision-makers. I'm also writing
        about urban policy, mostly focused on housing, transit, and what makes neighborhoods
        actually work for the people in them.
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- Contact / links -->
    <div class="mt-14 pt-8 border-t border-stone-200">
      <h2 class="font-display text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-4">
        Find me
      </h2>
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
        <a href="https://github.com/realtopophilia" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
           class="text-sm text-stone-600 hover:text-forest transition-colors">
          GitHub → realtopophilia
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
